Would be nice to have a function that returns whether a given string is in an array. This is useful to filter a list of objects by the value of a key. E.g.
```
{
    "Tags": [
        {
            "ResourceType": "instance",
            "ResourceId": "i-82h398h293g8h",
            "Value": "Test",
            "Key": "Application"
        },
        {
            "ResourceType": "instance",
            "ResourceId": "i-82h398h293g8h",
            "Value": "dev",
            "Key": "Environment"
        },
        {
            "ResourceType": "instance",
            "ResourceId": "i-82h398h293g8h",
            "Value": "testinstance",
            "Key": "Name"
        },
        {
            "ResourceType": "instance",
            "ResourceId": "i-82h398h293g8h",
            "Value": "mytier",
            "Key": "Tier"
        }
    ]
}
```

With the path: `Tags[?in(Key, ['Tier', 'Environment'])]`, will return:
```
{
    "Tags": [
        {
            "ResourceType": "instance",
            "ResourceId": "i-82h398h293g8h",
            "Value": "dev",
            "Key": "Environment"
        },
        {
            "ResourceType": "instance",
            "ResourceId": "i-82h398h293g8h",
            "Value": "mytier",
            "Key": "Tier"
        }
    ]
}
```

It's essentially the same as: `Tags[? Key == 'Tier' || Key == 'Environment']`, just nicer syntactic sugar.

